cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a transformation unit for visual recognition with deep convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of recognition tasks such as image classification, object detection, instance segmentation, and video classification. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new method for modeling channel relationships with explainable control variables, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also optimizes convolutional weights towards more accurate recognition, which is related to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also focuses on video classification, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
